#### 2. Underscore — triple-regex Replace chain + `.ToLower()` (4 allocations/call) 🔴 Critical

**Impact:** 3 intermediate string allocations from chained `Regex.Replace` + 1 from `.ToLower()` = 4 allocations per call on a millions-of-calls hot path.  
**File:** `CaseTransformExtensions.cs:L117-121`  
**Fix:** Consolidate into a single-pass `StringBuilder` or `Span<char>` scan that inserts underscores at case boundaries and lowercases in one pass:

```csharp
public static string Underscore(this string input)
{
    if (input.Length == 0) return input;
    var sb = new StringBuilder(input.Length + 4);
    for (int i = 0; i < input.Length; i++)
    {
        char c = input[i];
        if (c == '-' || c == ' ')
        {
            sb.Append('_');
        }
        else if (i > 0 && char.IsUpper(c))
        {
            char prev = input[i - 1];
            if (char.IsLower(prev) || char.IsDigit(prev))
                sb.Append('_');
            else if (i + 1 < input.Length && char.IsLower(input[i + 1]) && char.IsUpper(prev))
                sb.Append('_');
            sb.Append(char.ToLowerInvariant(c));
        }
        else
        {
            sb.Append(char.ToLowerInvariant(c));
        }
    }
    return sb.ToString();
}
```

This reduces 4 allocations → 1 (the final string).

